The paper focuses on emotion recognition using audio and visual modalities, which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and speech processing (cs.SD) fields. The use of deep learning models such as CNNs and LSTMs suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) as well. Additionally, the paper involves feature extraction and fusion, which are also relevant to multimedia processing (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
